                     <author key="n80013285" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/19703891/">Anṣārī al-Harawī, ʻAbd Allāh ibn Muḥammad, 1006-1089انصارى الهروى، عبد الله بن محمد</author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Munājāt</title>
                     
                     <title xml:lang="fa">مناجات</title>
                     <note>Bound with Codrington/Reade No 350 (2). F1a: a) Large round seal of Ayyub khanahzad of Muhammad Shah, dated A.H. 1132 (1719-20), regnal year one. Standing next to title written in bold naskh. b) Note evidently referring to eighteenth-century restorantion mentioning 44 folios including ? written ones. There is a similar note on the verso of the last folio of No 350 (2). c) Signature of David Price. Text is a prayer. The text areas of the folios of the sixteenth-century manuscript have been remounted on blue paper decorated with ruled borders and partly sprinkled with silver. The panel of illumination above the beginning of the text is probably from the original.</note>
                     <incipit>Ay zi dardat bi-dilan-a darman amadah</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, i, p. 35.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe, No 1779.</bibl>
